label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 219: Instruction pour les officiers de l'artillerie
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Treatise on artillery and explosives, as well as the construction of devices necessary for the construction and use of artillery and explosives. Concludes with several tables concerning distances and a detailed table of contents. A note in pencil on the last flyleaf refers to M. Robert, officier dans la marine; calculations in pencil inside lower cover; 2 notes in French with military references laid inside lower cover, one a note to Sergent Moulin, perhaps signed M. A. Gravitz.
        Language: French
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 18-25 long lines.
        Script: Written in cursive script by a single hand.
        Decoration: Table, p. 6
        Binding: Contemporary (18th-century) calf, gilt spine with title.
        Origin: Written in France after 1720 (latest date in text, p. 369).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 219
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5831589 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5831589
